<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-11-01T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-11-01T15:00:00-05:00" n="79" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.51/1193: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bundy</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-11-01T15:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November 1,
                                        1920—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>51. Your 73, October 21, 8 am.</p>
                        <p>Department approves the attitude of the Financial Adviser in stating to
                            the manager of the Bank of British West Africa that an attempt of the
                            Liberian Government to raise a loan without first consulting with him
                            would be a violation of the provisions of the Reform Program and the
                            1912 Agreement. Should the Department subsequently agree to receive the
                            proposed commission, the Financial Adviser should then approve loan.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
